#h1{#furigana{敬語}{けいご} — Keigo (Polite Language)}

Japanese has three levels of keigo:
#ul{
	#li{#strong{#furigana{丁寧語}{ていねいご}} — Polite language (ます/です forms, used with anyone)}
	#li{#strong{#furigana{尊敬語}{そんけいご}} — Respectful language (elevates the listener/subject's actions)}
	#li{#strong{#furigana{謙譲語}{けんじょうご}} — Humble language (lowers the speaker's own actions)}
}

#h2{#furigana{丁寧語}{ていねいご} — Polite Language}

Basic polite forms used in everyday formal speech.

